For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Statements made by counsel.

Defendant sentenced to serve 120 DAYS in the House of Correction with credit for 0 days time served.  Huber privileges under Sec.303.08 Wis. Stats. to apply for work. 

Court IMPOSED AND STAYED the sentence and placed Defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR with the following conditions:
*  No new law violations reaching the level of a probable cause finding.
*  Cooperate with agent.
*  Pay costs, surcharges, assessments, supervision, and DNA fees during the period of probation. If revoked, Defendant shall pay up to 25% of prison funds. Failure to pay shall result in a Civil Judgment with tax intercept.
*  Maintain full time / part time employment and or schooling.
*  ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
*  AODA assessment and treatment.
*  Random urine screens.  No association with drug users, drug dealers, drug houses, or drug dealing.
*  Mental Health assessment and treatment, if deemed appropriate.
*  Pay restitution of $350.00 to the victim Carrie K.V. during the period of probation. If revoked, Defendant shall pay up to 25% of prison funds. Failure to pay shall result in a Civil Judgment with tax intercept.
*  No contact with the victim Carrie K.V. or her residence or place of employment.
*  Participate in a Cognitive Thinking Program.

Court will consider expungement if Defendant successfully completes ALL conditions of probation, including with no new law violations reaching the level of a probable cause finding.
